Hi Everyone,
During the APM seminar, I emphasized that your ability to formulate and del=
iver TIM projects, along with your critical skills, will be your key compet=
itive advantage. Keep this in mind as you enter the 3rd term of the TIM pro=
gram, where you'll complete TIMG 5110 (Project-Based Learning), and the 4th=
 term, where you'll work on your final project (TIMG 5901 for MENG, 5905 fo=
r MENT, 5907 for MABA, and 5908 for MDTE).
To give you a better sense of what TIM project opportunities look like and =
where they come from, I=92ve attached two files: one with the project oppor=
tunities that were available to 5110 students in Summer 2024, and another w=
ith the first set of opportunities available for this Fall. This number wil=
l grow significantly by the 6th week of this term.
Please take a moment to review the two files so you can get a clear idea of=
 how a TIM project begins and what the TIM students do. For context, this F=
all, 47 TIM students are working on completing their TIM projects, with 66 =
students expected in Winter, and 27 in the Summer. Altogether, the TIM prog=
ram will produce 138 project reports this academic year. Each project repor=
t documente the research the student conducted to deliver value to an ident=
ifiable client. These client-driven projects are the "secret sauce" of the =
students in the TIM program.
Remember, while courses are interesting and foundation building, your value=
 is determined by the novelty and impact of the research project you comple=
te. Start thinking about the research projects you will complete NOW! Do no=
t wait for the 3rd term to start looking for a research project. Start NOW!
If you have any questions, feel free to reach out!
Best regards,
Tony B.
